To solve the Sleeping Barber problem using semaphores, we can create `Semaphore` objects to control access to the waiting area, barber chairs, and to check if the barber is asleep or not. 

Here's a Java class implementing the Sleeping Barber problem:

```java
import java.util.concurrent.Semaphore;

public class SleepingBarber {
    private Semaphore barberSemaphore; // Semaphore for signaling the barber, it's initialized to 0 (barber is asleep)
    private Semaphore customerSemaphore; // Semaphore for the customer to wait or leave, it's initialized to 0 (no customers are waiting)
    private Semaphore waitingRoomSemaphore; // Semaphore for access to waiting chairs, it's initialized with the number of chairs (n)

    public SleepingBarber(int numOfChairs) {
        barberSemaphore = new Semaphore(0);
        customerSemaphore = new Semaphore(0);
        waitingRoomSemaphore = new Semaphore(numOfChairs);
    }

    // Barber thread calls this method
    public void runBarber() {
        while (true) {
            try {
                // Acquire customer semaphore (wait for customer, release customer semaphore)
                customerSemaphore.acquire();

                // Acquire waiting room semaphore (release a chair)
                waitingRoomSemaphore.release();

                // Perform haircut (for simplicity, no actual haircut code is included)
                System.out.println("Giving a haircut.");

                // Release barber semaphore (barber becomes available for next customer)
                barberSemaphore.release();
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            }
        }
    }

    // Customer threads call this method
    public void haircut() {
        // Try to acquire waiting room semaphore (check if there's an available chair)
        if (waitingRoomSemaphore.tryAcquire()) {
            try {
                // Sitting in the waiting room
                System.out.println("Customer sitting in the waiting room.");

                // Acquire customer semaphore (signal the barber)
                customerSemaphore.release();

                // Wait for the barber
                barberSemaphore.acquire();

                // Get a haircut
                System.out.println("Customer getting a haircut.");

            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            } finally {
                // Leave the waiting room
                System.out.println("Customer leaving the barber shop.");
                waitingRoomSemaphore.release();
            }
        } else {
            // No available chairs, customer leaves
            System.out.println("No available chairs. Customer leaves.");
        }
    }
}
```

